\title{Building Phishing Reporting Button Workflow}

\taxon{skill}

\tag{phishing-reporting}

\tag{email-security}

\tag{incident-response}

\tag{security-awareness}

\tag{outlook}

\tag{microsoft-365}

\tag{soar}

\meta{version}{"1.0"}

\meta{description}{Implement a phishing report button in email clients with automated triage workflow that analyzes user-reported suspicious emails and provides feedback to reporters.}

\subtree{
\title{Building Phishing Reporting Button Workflow}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\pre{\startverb
A phishing reporting button empowers users to flag suspicious emails directly from their email client, creating a critical feedback loop between end users and the security operations center. Microsoft's built-in Report button is now the recommended approach, replacing the deprecated Report Message and Report Phishing add-ins. When combined with automated triage using SOAR platforms, reported emails can be classified, IOCs extracted, and remediation actions taken within minutes. Organizations with effective phishing reporting programs see 70%+ report rates in phishing simulations.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{When deploying or configuring building phishing reporting button workflow capabilities in your environment}
\li{When establishing security controls aligned to compliance requirements}
\li{When building or improving security architecture for this domain}
\li{When conducting security assessments that require this implementation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Microsoft 365 or Google Workspace with administrative access}
\li{SOAR platform or automation capability (Microsoft Sentinel, Splunk SOAR, Cortex XSOAR)}
\li{Dedicated reporting mailbox for phishing submissions}
\li{Email security gateway with message retraction capability}
\li{Security awareness training platform for feedback loop}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Deploy Phishing Report Button}
\ul{
\li{Enable Microsoft built-in Report button via Security & Compliance Center}
\li{Configure user reported settings: route to reporting mailbox and Microsoft}
\li{For third-party: deploy KnowBe4 Phish Alert Button or Cofense Reporter}
\li{Verify button appears in Outlook desktop, web, and mobile clients}
\li{Configure report options: Report Phishing, Report Junk, Report Not Junk}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Build Automated Triage Pipeline}
\ul{
\li{Configure reporting mailbox monitored by SOAR platform}
\li{Auto-extract IOCs from reported emails: URLs, attachments, sender info, headers}
\li{Submit URLs to VirusTotal, URLScan.io for reputation check}
\li{Submit attachments to sandbox for dynamic analysis}
\li{Check sender against known threat intelligence feeds}
\li{Auto-classify: confirmed phishing, spam, simulation, legitimate}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Implement Response Actions}
\ul{
\li{Confirmed phishing: auto-retract from all inboxes, block sender domain}
\li{Confirmed spam: move to junk for all recipients}
\li{Simulation email: mark as correctly reported, credit user}
\li{Legitimate email: return to inbox, notify reporter}
\li{Generate IOC report for threat intelligence team}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 4: Create Feedback Loop}
\ul{
\li{Send automated thank-you response to reporter within 5 minutes}
\li{Include classification result when analysis completes}
\li{Track reporter accuracy and engagement metrics}
\li{Recognize top reporters in monthly security newsletter}
\li{Feed reporting metrics into security awareness training program}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 5: Measure and Optimize}
\ul{
\li{Track mean time to triage (target: under 10 minutes automated)}
\li{Monitor report volume trends and false positive rates}
\li{Measure user reporting rate in phishing simulations}
\li{Report on confirmed threats caught by user reports vs. gateway}
\li{Optimize automation rules based on classification accuracy}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tools & Resources}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Microsoft Report Button}: Built-in Outlook phishing reporting}
\li{\strong{Cofense Reporter + Triage}: Enterprise phishing reporting and automated analysis}
\li{\strong{KnowBe4 Phish Alert Button}: Integrated reporting with simulation platform}
\li{\strong{Microsoft Sentinel}: SOAR automation for triage workflow}
\li{\strong{Proofpoint CLEAR}: Closed-loop email analysis and response}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Validation}
\ul{
\li{Report button visible and functional across all Outlook platforms}
\li{Reported email arrives in dedicated mailbox within 60 seconds}
\li{Automated triage classifies test phishing email correctly}
\li{Auto-retraction removes confirmed phishing from all inboxes}
\li{Reporter receives feedback notification with classification}
\li{Metrics dashboard shows report volume and accuracy trends}
}
}
}